Usage

- With Alembic (preferred):
  1) Ensure DATABASE_URL is set (or in alembic.ini), e.g.
     postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/alumni_platform
  2) From backend/: run
     alembic upgrade head

- With Docker Compose:
  1) Start services: docker compose up -d db
  2) Set DATABASE_URL to point to db service:
     postgresql://postgres:password@db:5432/alumni_platform
  3) Run migrations inside backend container or host with env set:
     alembic upgrade head

- Apply raw SQL directly (psql):
  psql "$DATABASE_URL" -f migrations/sql/schema.sql



